SIMPLE: mousing
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mousing
<hw>Mous"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Impertinently
inquisitive; prying; meddlesome.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Mousing</xex>
saints.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mousing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mousing
<hw>Mous"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of hunting
mice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A turn or lashing of spun yarn or
small stuff, or a metallic clasp or fastening, uniting the point and
shank of a hook to prevent its unhooking or straighening out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A ratchet movement in a loom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mousing hook</b></col>, <cd>a hook with an attachment
which prevents its unhooking.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mousle</ent>⟦br⟧
